---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../../components/HeroSection.astro';
import SignupForm from '../../components/SignupForm.astro';
import { donateUrl } from '../../data/navigation';
---

<PageLayout title="Health | Fatmata Barrie" description="Fatmata Barrie's platform on healthcare access, mental health, and health equity for Montgomery County residents.">

  <HeroSection title="Health" subtitle="Every Montgomery County resident deserves access to quality, affordable, culturally competent care." />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container priority-layout">

      <div class="priority-body">

        <p class="priority-intro">
          Good health is the foundation of everything else — a stable life, a productive career, a thriving family. But too many Montgomery County residents face rising costs, provider shortages, and systems that weren't built with them in mind. Fatmata will invest in community-centered health care that meets people where they are — regardless of income, insurance status, or language.
        </p>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Expand Access to Affordable Healthcare</h2>
          <p>Health insurance doesn't guarantee health care. Even insured residents face high deductibles, limited in-network providers, and facilities that are far from home or work. Uninsured and underinsured residents often delay care until a crisis — at far greater human and financial cost.</p>
          <p>Fatmata will push to expand funding for community health clinics and Federally Qualified Health Centers (FQHCs), which provide affordable, high-quality care regardless of a patient's ability to pay. She will work to increase the county's outreach and enrollment efforts for Medicaid and other public health insurance programs.</p>
          <p>For many residents — particularly those working multiple jobs or living far from the nearest clinic — even getting to an appointment can be a barrier in itself. Fatmata will work to strengthen community-based healthcare services so that residents can access care close to home, regardless of where they live in the county.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Address the Youth Mental Health Crisis</h2>
          <p>Montgomery County, like communities across the country, is experiencing a serious youth mental health crisis. Rates of anxiety, depression, and suicidal ideation have risen sharply, and there are not enough child and adolescent mental health providers to meet demand.</p>
          <p>Fatmata will fight to expand school-based mental health services, increase funding for county mental health programs, and reduce the stigma around seeking help. Mental health is health — and it must be treated that way.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Mental Health</h2>
          <p>Mental health needs are rising across Montgomery County, while access to care has not kept pace. Too many residents face long wait times, provider shortages, and barriers such as cost, transportation, and language.</p>
          <p>Fatmata will work to expand access to community-based mental health services, strengthen crisis response systems, and support efforts to grow and diversify the behavioral health workforce. She will also prioritize outreach and education to reduce stigma and ensure residents can access care when and where they need it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Strengthen Language Access and Culturally Competent Care</h2>
          <p>Montgomery County is one of the most linguistically diverse jurisdictions in the nation — including residents who are Deaf or hard of hearing and rely on American Sign Language (ASL) or Black American Sign Language (BASL). Yet health care systems often fail patients who don't communicate in spoken English — through inadequate interpretation services, culturally mismatched care, and systems designed for a different patient population.</p>
          <p>Fatmata will fight to expand language access services — including interpretation in ASL and BASL — across county health programs, support culturally competent training for providers, and ensure that every resident can communicate effectively with their health care team.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Why This Matters for Montgomery County</h2>
          <p>Health inequities cost our county — in lost productivity, emergency room overcrowding, preventable hospitalizations, and human suffering. Investing in preventive, community-centered care is not just the right thing to do — it's the smart thing to do. A healthier county is a stronger county.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-closing">
          <p>No one in Montgomery County should go without care because of cost, language, or geography. Fatmata will fight to build a health system that truly works for all of us — not just some of us.</p>
          <div class="priority-cta-buttons">
            <a href={donateUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-accent">Donate to the Campaign</a>
            <a href="/volunteer" class="btn btn-primary">Get Involved</a>
            <a href="/priorities" class="btn btn-outline">Back to All Priorities</a>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <aside class="priority-sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar-card">
          <h3>Key Actions</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Expand access to affordable healthcare services</li>
            <li>Address the youth mental health crisis</li>
            <li>Expand access to mental health services</li>
            <li>Strengthen language access and culturally competent care</li>
            <li>Strengthen community-based care so residents can access services close to home, regardless of where they live</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar-card sidebar-nav">
          <h3>Other Priorities</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/priorities/affordability">Affordability &amp; Housing</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/business">Business &amp; Economy</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/climate">Climate Justice</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/democracy">Defending Democracy</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/education">Education</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/safety">Safer Communities</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/transportation">Transportation</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/seniors">Seniors &amp; Aging</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/womens-health">Women's Health</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </div>
  </section>

  <SignupForm />

</PageLayout>

<style>
  .priority-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .priority-intro {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-light);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--teal);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .priority-section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }

  .priority-section h2 { font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem); color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

  .priority-section p { color: var(--text); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

  .priority-closing {
    background: var(--cream);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .priority-closing p { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

  .priority-cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  .btn-outline {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.5rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--primary);
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: var(--primary);
    font-family: var(--font-primary);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    transition: all var(--transition);
  }

  .btn-outline:hover { background: var(--primary); color: var(--white); }

  .priority-sidebar { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; position: sticky; top: 90px; }

  .sidebar-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }

  .sidebar-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-primary);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .sidebar-card ul { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }

  .sidebar-card ul li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.5;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .sidebar-card ul li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.5rem;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
  }

  .sidebar-nav ul li::before { background: var(--teal); }
  .sidebar-nav ul li a { color: var(--primary); font-size: 0.9rem; transition: color var(--transition); }
  .sidebar-nav ul li a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .priority-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .priority-sidebar { position: static; }
    .priority-cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; }
    .priority-cta-buttons .btn { text-align: center; }
  }
</style>
